from sklearn import datasets, linear_model
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

# View per gender
height_m = df.loc[df.gender == 'M']
height_f = df.loc[df.gender == 'F']
temp_l = [height_m, height_f]

# Initialization
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

# data
ax.scatter(y= height_m.height, x= height_m.Avg_parent, label= 'Male')
ax.scatter(y= height_f.height, x= height_f.Avg_parent, label= 'Female')



# regression

######## NUMPY way
y = temp_l[0].height
x = temp_l[0].Avg_parent

residuals_all = []

X = np.stack((np.ones(len(x)),x), axis= 1)
a, b = np.linalg.inv(X.T @ X) @X.T @ y
r_xs = np.linspace(x.min(), x.max())
regression_ys = a + b * x

RSS = np.sum(np.square(y - regression_ys))
TSS = np.sum(np.square(y - np.mean(y)))
residuals = y - regression_ys
residuals_all.append(residuals)

R2 = 1 - (RSS/TSS)

# plot regression line
# ax.plot(r_xs, a+b * r_xs, c='yellow', label = f"boy R^2= {round(R2, 4)}", linewidth= 3)
print(f"Numpy way \nboy R^2= {round(R2, 4)}")

########### SciKit way
y = temp_l[0].height.to_numpy().reshape(-1, 1)
x = temp_l[0].Avg_parent.to_numpy().reshape(-1, 1)

# Create linear regression object
regr_height = linear_model.LinearRegression()

# Train the model using the training sets
regr_height.fit(x, y)

### UNLEASH!!
y_pred = regr_height.predict(x)

# The coefficients
print("\nScikit way:\nCoefficients: \n", regr_height.coef_)
# The mean squared error
print("Mean squared error: %.2f" % mean_squared_error(y, y_pred))
# The coefficient of determination: 1 is perfect prediction
scikit_r2 = r2_score(y, y_pred)
print("Coefficient of determination: %.2f" % r2_score(y, y_pred))

# Plot regression line
plt.plot(x, y_pred, color="blue", linewidth=1, label = f"boy R^2= {round(scikit_r2, 4)}")

#####################

plt.xlabel('average parent length')
plt.ylabel('height child')

ax.legend(title= 'Gender', bbox_to_anchor= (1.3,1 ))

plt.show()

# Extract features, thus excluding height
values = df.iloc[:, 1:]

# Normalize (std of 1, mean is not on origin)
X = (values - values.mean(axis=0)) / values.std(axis=0)

# Extract eigenvalues and eigenvectors
vals, vecs = np.linalg.eigh(np.cov(X.T))
order = vals.argsort()[::-1]
vals = vals[order]
vecs = vecs[:, order]
